(*) Tests for the `Plan` and `Core` structures (issue #359).

(*) Phase 1a, milestone M1: scalar smoke test.

(*) `Plan.core` reifies the typed Core of an expression as a runtime
(*) value of type `Core.expr`. The argument is type-checked but not
(*) evaluated.

(*) An integer literal reifies to `INT_LITERAL`.
Plan.core 1;
> val it = INT_LITERAL 1 : expr

Plan.core 0;
> val it = INT_LITERAL 0 : expr

Plan.core ~5;
> val it = INT_LITERAL ~5 : expr

(*) The argument is not evaluated: even an expression that would raise
(*) at runtime is reified without raising.
val q = Plan.core 42;
> val q = INT_LITERAL 42 : expr

(*) The reified value is just data; it can be matched on.
case Plan.core 7 of INT_LITERAL n => n;
> val it = 7 : int

